                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. CRAUFURD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">E. LLOYD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770625-name-71" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-71" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-71" type="surname" value="NASH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-71" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN NASH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barmaid at the Apple Tree public-house, Mount Pleasant, Clerkenwell—on 19th May the prisoner called for a quartern of gin and tendered a bad sovereign—I gave it to Mr. Reynolds, who gave him in charge—he said he took it of his governor in Fetter Lans; I forget the name.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770625-name-72" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-72" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-72" type="surname" value="REYNOLDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-72" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>MICHAEL REYNOLDS</persName>
                  </hi>. The last witness called my attention to a bad sovereign—I asked the prisoner about it; he made no reply—I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770625-name-73" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-73" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-73" type="surname" value="BARLOW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770625-name-73" type="given" value="ISAAH"></interp>ISAAH BARLOW</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman G</hi> 105). I took the prisoner into custody—he said he received the coin from his employer in Fetter Lane; I forget" the name—then he said he got in change for a 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note—I found three sixpences on him and 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. good money—he told me on the 23rd to go to Speight's in Fetter Lane, and after that to a Mr. Hawkins.</p>
